title: Associate Hole primitive with parent pcb_component_id
description: Associates Hole primitives with their parents pcb_component_id to ensure correct placement during auto-layout.
body:
This change ensures that Hole primitives are correctly associated with their parent's pcb_component_id during     
rendering.                                                                                                        

Previously, pcb_hole elements created from Hole primitives within a component's footprint were not linked to the  
parent PCB component. This caused them to be misplaced during auto-layout, as they were not treated as part of the
component.                                                                                                        

The fix resolves this by assigning the parent's pcb_component_id to the pcb_hole upon creation, which corrects the
behavior in the flashlight panel auto-layout test.

title: Fix silkscreen rect PCB translation in footprints
description: Fixes incorrect positioning of silkscreen rectangles in footprints by using the global PCB transform instead of local offsets.
body:
### Motivation
- Silkscreen rect primitives inside footprints were using their local `pcbX`/`pcbY` resolution and not the full parent/global PCB transform.
- That caused silkscreen rects placed via a `<footprint>` (e.g. inside a `<chip>`) to not follow the chip's `pcbX`/`pcbY` offsets.
- The change ensures footprint primitives are positioned according to the composed/global PCB transform so they move with their parent component.

### Description
- Use the global transform position for silkscreen rects by replacing `getResolvedPcbPositionProp()` with `_getGlobalPcbPositionBeforeLayout()` in `lib/components/primitive-components/SilkscreenRect.ts`.
- Add a test `SilkscreenRect footprint positions respect chip pcbX/pcbY` in `tests/components/primitive-components/silkscreen-rect.test.tsx` that places a `<silkscreenrect>` inside a `<chip footprint>` and asserts the translated center coordinates.
- Minor formatting and committed the updated files.

### Testing
- Ran `BUN_UPDATE_SNAPSHOTS=1 bun test tests/components/primitive-components/silkscreen-rect.test.tsx` â€” 2 tests passed (the original rendering test and the new footprint position test).
- Ran `bunx tsc --noEmit` for type checking â€” succeeded.
- Ran `bun run format` â€” formatting completed successfully.

title: Fix assignable obstacle layer traversal
description: Fixes autorouting failure by constraining assignable obstacles to their declared layers, preventing routing onto layers where it should not occur.
body:
### Motivation
- Assignable via obstacles declared with specific `layers` were being treated as spanning all Z layers, allowing routing onto the `bottom` layer when they should not. 
- This caused traces to appear on the bottom layer for nets that are only assignable on the `top` layer. 
- Add a regression test from the bug report to prevent regressions. 

### Description
- Constrain created assignable-obstacle nodes to the obstacle's declared `layers` by mapping layer names to Z indices with `mapLayerNameToZ` and using those indices as `availableZ` instead of always spanning all layers. 
- Preserve the previous fallback behavior when an obstacle has no `layers` specified, retaining the old full-span behavior. 
- Add the bug report payload, a fixture (`examples/bug-reports/bugreport26-66b0b2`), an SVG snapshot (`tests/bugs/__snapshots__/bugreport26-66b0b2.snap.svg`), and a snapshot test (`tests/bugs/bugreport26-66b0b2.test.ts`). 
- Run project formatting (`bun run format`) to normalize code style.

### Testing
- `BUN_UPDATE_SNAPSHOTS=1 bun test tests/bugs/bugreport26-66b0b2.test.ts` generated/updated the SVG snapshot and passed. 
- `bunx tsc --noEmit` was run and reported type errors in unrelated test files (`tests/core*.test.tsx`), so full typecheck did not pass. 
- `bun run format` completed successfully and formatted files.

description: Calculates the bounding box of a PCB board using its outline and updates texture generation logic to ensure accurate sizing and positioning for non-rectangular boards.
body: This pull request introduces a new utility for calculating the true bounding box of a PCB board, using its outline when available, and refactors all texture generation and rendering logic to use these outline-based bounds instead of relying solely on the boardâ€™s rectangular dimensions. This ensures that textures and meshes are accurately sized and positioned for boards with non-rectangular outlines, improving visual fidelity and correctness. ### Board outline bounds calculation and usage * Added the new `calculateOutlineBounds` utility in `src/utils/outline-bounds.ts`, which computes the bounding box, width, height, and center of a board either from its outline or falls back to its rectangular dimensions. * Refactored texture generation functions (`createSilkscreenTextureForLayer`, `createSoldermaskTextureForLayer`, `createTraceTextureForLayer`) to use outline-based bounds for canvas sizing and coordinate conversion, ensuring textures match the actual board shape. description: Simplifies how the latest CDN URLs are provided for both tscircuitcircuit-preview and tscircuit by replacing dynamic fetching with static URLs from jsdelivr, removing related state and effects in hooks.
body:

Instead of dynamically fetching the latest version from external APIs at runtime, the hooks now return fixed CDN URLs pointing to the latest package versions on jsdelivr. title: Disable parts engine when BOM is disabled
description: Disables parts engine supplier lookups when BOM is intentionally turned off by checking the bomDisabled flag in group props.
body:
### Motivation

- The `bomDisabled` flag in group props should disable BOM/parts-engine behavior to avoid supplier lookups when BOM is intentionally turned off.
- Parts engine supplier lookups may perform network/cache operations that should be skipped when BOM is disabled.
- The `@tscircuit/props` package was updated to expose the `bomDisabled` property in the inherited props chain.
- Preventing unnecessary parts lookups reduces noise and potential errors when BOM is disabled.

### Description

- Bumped `@tscircuit/props` dependency to `^0.0.435` in `package.json` to pick up `bomDisabled` typings.
- Added an inherited-property check `if (this.getInheritedProperty("bomDisabled")) return` to `doInitialPartsEngineRender` to skip initial supplier lookups when BOM is disabled.
- Added the same inherited-property check to `updatePartsEngineRender` to avoid updating supplier data when BOM is disabled.
- No other behavior changes; existing `doNotPlace` guarding remains in place.

### Testing

- Ran typecheck with `bunx tsc --noEmit`, which completed successfully.
- Ran formatter with `bun run format`, which completed successfully.
- Executed `bun update --latest @tscircuit/props` to update the dependency, which completed successfully.
- No unit tests were added or modified for this change.

- This change causes the persisted `num_layers`/`allLayers.length` used when generating `SimpleRouteJson` to be correct for single-layer boards.

title: Add Galvo Laser Frequency and Pulse Width Support to CutSetting (LightBurn/EZCAD2 Compatible)
description: Adds support for frequency and pulseWidth parameters in the CutSetting class to enable compatibility with LightBurns galvo-specific laser settings for EZCAD2BSL boards.
body:
### Added support for frequency and pulseWidth parameters in the CutSetting class to enable compatibility with LightBurn's galvo-specific laser settings for EZCAD2/BSL boards.
## Changes
- CutSettingInit interface: Added optional frequency?: number and pulseWidth?: number fields
- CutSetting class: Added private fields _frequency and _pulseWidth with corresponding getters/setters
- Constructor: Updated to initialize the new parameters from init object
- XML serialization: Added frequency and pulseWidth to the props array for proper XML output
- XML parsing: Added parsing logic in fromXmlJson() to read frequency and pulseWidth from LBRN files
- Tests: Added comprehensive tests for serialization and roundtrip parsing of the new parameters Compatibility
- Backwards compatible: Existing code and LBRN files continue to work unchanged
- Units: frequency in Hz, pulseWidth in seconds
- Optional fields: Maintains existing API contract Files Modified
- lib/classes/elements/CutSetting.ts
- tests/getString-xml.test.ts 
- tests/roundtrip-xml.test.ts

This enables programmable laser pulsing parameters for advanced cutting operations in galvo laser systems.
